ariables (see pdp.data.ts):\n253: //   TEST_USER_EMAIL / TEST_USER_PASSWORD\n254: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n255: test(\n256:     'TC-83240 — Authenticated user adds product to wishlist and API call confirms the action @pdp @wishlist @authenticated',\n257:     async ({ page }) => {\n258:         const loginPage = new LoginPage(page);\n259:         const homePage = new HomePage(page);\n260:         const searchResultsPage = new SearchResultsPage(page);\n261:         const pdpPage = new ProductDetailPage(page);\n262: \n263:         // ── Precondition: Log in ────────────────────────────────────────────\n264:         await test.step('Log in with test user credentials', async () => {\n265:             await loginPage.login(pdpData.auth.email, pdpData.auth.password);\n266:         });\n267: \n268:         // ── Navigate to a vitamins PDP ──────────────────────────────────────\n269:         await test.step('Navigate to a vitamins product detail page via search', async () => {"}}
[12:41:59] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "Let me analyze the three failures:\n\n**1. TC-83232 — Newsletter signup (chromium + edge)**\n- Selector: `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` \n- The scroll loop runs 5x then does `waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 })` but still times out\n- The issue: the newsletter input may be in an iframe, or the selector is wrong for this environment, or the page renders it differently\n- Looking at HomePage, need to check the `newsletterEmailInput` locator\n\n**2. TC-83238 — In-Store Pickup (firefox + webkit)**\n- The OLD code: `await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });`\n- But the current ProductDetailPage.ts code at line 262 shows the NEW method `openStoreSelectorDialog()` which has better fallback logic (tries \"Set your store\" for 3s, then falls back to \"Check Availability at other stores\")\n- The error says `pages/ProductDetailPage.ts:262` but in the current file line 262 is inside `openStoreSelectorDialog()` at the `await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor` — but wait, looking at the current file, line 262 is `await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });`... but the current file shows line 262 is `await this.inStorePickupRadio.scrollIntoViewIfNeeded(...)`.\n- Actually the traceback says `ProductDetailPage.ts:262` which is `await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor(...)`. But the current file at line 262 shows the improved method. So the traceback is from an older version of the file. The current file IS already fixed with the fallback logic.\n\nWait - let me re-read. The error traceback shows:\n```\nat ../pages/ProductDetailPage.ts:262\n260 |      */\n261 |     async openStoreSelectorDialog(): Promise<void> {\n> 262 |         await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });\n```\n\nBut the CURRENT file has:\n```\n270:     async openStoreSelectorDialog(): Promise<void> {\n271:         // Scroll the fulfillment area into view so lazy-rendered elements mount.\n272:         await this.inStorePickupRadio\n273:             .scrollIntoViewIfNeeded({ timeout: 10_000 })\n```\n\nSo the current file already has the improved version. The error is from a PREVIOUS run. The current code should handle this.\n\nBUT — the issue description says these are CURRENT failures. So either:\n- The test was run with the old code, or\n- The new code still has issues\n\nLet me look at the current `openStoreSelectorDialog()` more carefully:\n- Line 283-285: `isVisible({ timeout: 3_000 })` — this uses `isVisible` which doesn't wait, it just checks immediately. The 3_000 timeout might be causing issues...\n\nActually `isVisible(options)` with a timeout was deprecated in Playwright, or might behave differently. The correct approach is `waitFor`. Let me check.\n\nActually `isVisible()` in Playwright doesn't take a timeout in the same way — it returns immediately. The `{ timeout: 3_000 }` option is not standard for `isVisible()`. This would always return immediately (false if not visible) and not wait at all.\n\nSo the fallback to `checkAvailabilityLink` would happen immediately. But then `checkAvailabilityLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 12_000 })` would also fail if neither link is present yet.\n\nThe real issue for TC-83238 on firefox/webkit: The page may not be fully hydrated when `openStoreSelectorDialog()` is called. The `inStorePickupRadio.scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` fails silently, then `isVisible` checks immediately and returns false (since elements aren't mounted), and then `checkAvailabilityLink.waitFor` times out.\n\n**Fix for TC-83238:**\n- After scrolling into view, wait a bit for elements to mount\n- Or: wait for either \"set your store\" OR \"check availability\" link to become visible before checking which one to click\n- Better: use `Promise.race` or `waitForSelector` with a longer timeout to detect which link appears\n\n**3. TC-83240 — Wishlist authenticated (chromium + edge)**  \n- LoginPage.ts:28: `await this.emailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });`\n- But current LoginPage.ts line 34 shows `timeout: 30_000`\n- So current file is already updated with 30s timeout.\n- The error might be stale from before the fix.\n\nBut since the task says \"fix these issues\", I should look at what's happening NOW. The traceback shows line 28 with 15_000 timeout — but current code has 30_000. So these failures might be from the PREVIOUS test run, and the current code already has some fixes.\n\nHowever, re-reading the task:\n- \"FIx this issues\" — the user is showing me current failures and wants them fixed\n- The current code may have been partially fixed between runs\n\nLet me check what the actual issues are:\n\n**Issue 1: TC-83232 Newsletter**\n- Need to see the `newsletterEmailInput` locator in HomePage\n- The selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` is timing out\n- The scroll loop runs but still can't find it\n\n**Issue 2: TC-83238 In-Store Pickup on Firefox/WebKit**\n- On these browsers, the site may auto-detect location and pre-select a store\n- The `isVisible({ timeout: 3_000 })` for setYourStoreLink is problematic\n- Need better detection logic\n\n**Issue 3: TC-83240 Login**\n- The login form email input isn't visible within timeout\n- Could be a page-load issue or wrong URL redirect\n\nLet me read the HomePage class to understand the newsletter selector, and then look at the current test error contexts if available.\n"}}
